cs.HC, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.AI 

This paper proposes a model for usability, which is a key aspect of human-computer interaction (HCI). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also discusses the quality assurance process, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering). The use of a meta-model and the focus on system properties and user activities could also place it in cs.CY (Computational Geometry) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper mentions the automatic generation of guideline documents, which could indicate a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
